Just to explain what happens here: if jsonValue has no key "Drives" it will return reference to empty nlohmann::json object and in line 54 empty array is assigned to it.

Since there maybe be some errors later on you should do it at the end of async_method_call when you are sure that this async_method_call exuted without errors.

if (ec) { ... }

nlohmann::json storageArray = nlohmann::json::array();

// .. fill storageArray

asyncResp->res.jsonValue["Drives@odata.count"] = storageArray.size();
asyncResp->res.jsonValue["Drives"] = std::move(storageArray);

